Part of what makes Camp Forget-Me-Not/Camp Erin DC truly special are the personalized touches our campers receive. From the interaction with their buddy to the smaller items that they can take home that remind them of their healing experience at camp. 

Today, New York Life Insurance Company employees, led by camp volunteer Dominique Duong, generously donated blankets and hand-made luggage tags to our campers. We are so grateful for their time and commitment to camp!
